{"generated":"2026-03-21T20:16:05.509062+00:00","period_start":"2026-03-15T18:51:00+00:00","period_end":"2026-03-21T20:11:00+00:00","snapshot_count":90,"html":"<h1>THE VENDETTA GAZETTE</h1>\n<h2>MARCH 22, 2026 • SPECIAL EDITION • \"ALL THE NEWS THAT'S FIT TO BOOTLEG\"</h2>\n\n<h3>TWIN TERRORS TEAR THROUGH TURF IN BLOODIEST WEEK YET!</h3>\n\n<p><strong>Sir Caprice \"The Gentleman Slayer\" and Wu-Tang \"The Iron Fist\" carve up Vendetta City in reign of terror</strong></p>\n\n<p>Hold onto your tommy guns, dear readers, for this scribe has witnessed the most spectacular display of criminal carnage since the Great Valentine's Day Massacre of '24! The streets of Vendetta City ran red with the blood of fallen syndicates as two ruthless overlords divided the spoils between themselves like Caesar and Pompey splitting the Roman Empire.</p>\n\n<p>Leading this week's parade of pandemonium, the dapper devil known as <strong>Sir Caprice \"The Gentleman Slayer\"</strong> seized a staggering <em>97 territories</em> while simultaneously orchestrating the fall of <em>13 rival headquarters</em>. Not to be outdone, the mysterious Oriental menace <strong>Wu-Tang \"The Iron Fist of Chinatown\"</strong> matched Caprice turf-for-turf with his own 97 conquests, backed by an earth-shaking <em>17 HQ demolitions</em> that left rival bosses weeping into their bootleg whiskey.</p>\n\n<p>These twin titans of terror have transformed Vendetta City's criminal landscape, with lesser kingpins scrambling like rats from a sinking speakeasy. The Vacation Brothers—<strong>Steve and Albert</strong>—managed respectable hauls of 48 and 40 territories respectively, while the bloodthirsty <strong>Blood Captain</strong> lived up to his crimson moniker with 28 fresh conquests.</p>\n\n<p>Meanwhile, the fallen mighty tell a tale of woe that would make a funeral director weep with joy. Poor <strong>StreetKing</strong>, once the toast of the underworld, saw his empire crumble by 27 territories. The grandly-named <strong>FIFTH BLOOD EMPEROR</strong> proved that imperial titles don't stop bullets, losing 22 prime lots to hungrier predators.</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n<h3>SPECIAL BULLETIN: THE IRON FIST STRIKES!</h3>\n<p><strong>WU-TANG'S WEDNESDAY RAMPAGE LEAVES FOUR HQs IN RUINS!</strong></p>\n<p>In a display of strategic brilliance that would make Sun Tzu himself tip his hat, Wu-Tang \"The Iron Fist\" orchestrated a lightning campaign on March 20th that saw <em>four rival headquarters</em> reduced to smoking rubble in a single day! The Oriental mastermind's forces swept through Aharhibaba's fortress, demolished 2345p's stronghold, and left Muna's once-proud HQ a pile of matchsticks. This reporter's sources whisper that Wu-Tang's boys moved with military precision, striking before dawn and vanishing like ghosts in the morning mist.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<h3>FRESH FACES AND FAMILIAR CORPSES</h3>\n\n<p>The week brought six new desperados crawling out of the woodwork, led by the war-painted <strong>John James Rambo</strong> and the space-age gunslinger <strong>Flash Gordon</strong>. Each staked their claim to a single territory, proving that even in these dark times, the American Dream of criminal enterprise burns bright.</p>\n\n<p>But for every fresh face, the reaper claimed nearly eight veteran souls. Forty-five established operators vanished into the ether, their territories absorbed by hungrier wolves. The streets whisper that some fled to Chicago, others to cement shoes at the bottom of the harbor.</p>\n\n<hr>\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"640\" height=\"276\" style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;background:#0a0800;display:block;margin:18px auto\">\n<text x=\"320\" y=\"22\" text-anchor=\"middle\" fill=\"#c8a84a\" font-size=\"13\" font-weight=\"bold\" letter-spacing=\"2\" font-family=\"Georgia,serif\">TERRITORY GAINS THIS WEEK</text>\n<line x1=\"20\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"620\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#3a2a00\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>\n<text x=\"154\" y=\"48\" text-anchor=\"end\