\">Cokro</text>\n<rect x=\"160\" y=\"203\" width=\"74\" height=\"16\" fill=\"#c8a84a\" opacity=\"0.85\"/>\n<text x=\"240\" y=\"216\" fill=\"#c8a84a\" font-size=\"11\" font-family=\"Georgia,serif\">+18</text>\n<text x=\"154\" y=\"244\" text-anchor=\"end\" fill=\"#a09060\" font-size=\"11\" font-family=\"Georgia,serif\">SCRIPTUS</text>\n<rect x=\"160\" y=\"231\" width=\"74\" height=\"16\" fill=\"#c8a84a\" opacity=\"0.85\"/>\n<text x=\"240\" y=\"244\" fill=\"#c8a84a\" font-size=\"11\" font-family=\"Georgia,serif\">+18</text>\n</svg>\n\n\n<h3>POLICE BLOTTER</h3>\n\n<p><em>Officer Murphy reports arresting a gentleman who claimed to be \"Donald Trump, Real Estate Mogul\" after he was caught trying to put gold nameplates on 20 fire hydrants he insisted he now owned.</em></p>\n\n<p><em>The 42nd Precinct investigated reports of a man calling himself \"SCRIPTUS\" attempting to copyright the rights to several street corners, armed only with a briefcase full of legal documents and a very sharp pencil.</em></p>\n\n<p><em>Vacation Bob was spotted at three different crime scenes this week, leading detectives to conclude he's either the world's unluckiest tourist or the world's most obvious criminal mastermind.</em></p>\n<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"640\" height=\"276\" style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;background:#0a0800;display:block;margin:18px auto\">\n<text x=\"320\" y=\"22\" text-anchor=\"middle\" fill=\"#c8a84a\" font-size=\"13\" font-weight=\"bold\" letter-spacing=\"2\" font-family=\"Georgia,serif\">HEAVIEST LOSSES THIS WEEK</text>\n<line x1=\"20\" y1=\"28\" x2=\"620\" y2=\"28\" stroke=\"#3a2a00\" stroke-width=\"1\"/>\n<text x=\"154\" y=\"48\" text-anchor=\"end\" fill=\"#a09060\" font-size=\"11\" font-family=\"Georgia,serif\">StreetKing</text>\n<rect x=\"160\" y=\"35\" width=\"400\" height=\"16\" fill=\"#8b1a1a\" opacity=\"0.85\"/>\n<text x=\"566\" y=\"48\" fill=\"#8b1a1a\" font-size=\"11\" font-family=\"Georgia,serif\">-27</text>\n<text x=\"154\" y=\"76